oai_dc:dc.dc:description: SPC 2014.010.001 Stereograph view of the Funeral of Ex-President Andrew Johnson at Greeneville, Tenn. August 3d, 1875. Court House where the remains were Lying in State. The Hearse in front waiting for the delayed train from Knoxville. From Brown’s Building looking South-East. A series of 12 of these views taken on the same day form an interesting and comprehensive idea of the occasion. Greeneville, &c., surroundings. Published by L.W. Keen, Photographer, Jonesboro’, Tenn. SPC 2014.010.001 b back of stereograph with ID information.
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: Funeral processions; Funeral rites & ceremonies; Presidents; Stereographs;
